messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full HTTP request path:
- /cms/admin/user/{uid}/password

Method support (based on code only):
- All HTTP methods allowed? No
- HEAD: Not acceptable (route is defined with PUT; HEAD is not explicitly supported by the code)
- POST: Not acceptable
- OPTIONS: Acceptable (Flask provides automatic OPTIONS handling for routes)
- TRACE: Not acceptable
- GET: Not acceptable
- PUT: Acceptable
- DELETE: Not acceptable
- PATCH: Not acceptable

Explanation:
- The change_user_password endpoint is declared in app/api/cms/admin.py with the route "/user/<int:uid>/password" and methods=["PUT"] on the admin blueprint.
- This admin blueprint is registered under the cms blueprint with url_prefix="/admin", which itself is mounted on the cms blueprint with url_prefix="/cms" in app/__init__.py. Therefore, the full path becomes /cms/admin/user/{uid}/password.
- Because the route explicitly accepts only PUT, only PUT is supported by the code. Flask will automatically handle OPTIONS for this route (unless disabled), but there is no explicit support for HEAD in this route since HEAD is not defined for PUT-only routes.
